main event: On October 6, 1955, two large radar blips were observed in Columbus, Ohio, but no aircraft could be visually identified.
interesting points: The radar blips moved in a zigzag path,The observation was made over a 30-minute period,The sighting had ground-radar type observation,There was a suggestion that the blips could possibly be aircraft, but data was insufficient for definitive conclusions.
witness description: S/SGT James Whitehead, finance at LCK PD
